Male Sterility inherited
Type of Male Sterility
1. Genetic Male Sterility (GMS)
2. Cytoplasmic Male Sterility (CMS)
3. Cytoplasmic-Genetic male sterility (CGMS)
GMS (Genetic Male Sterility)
1. Nuclear - gene , control
It is controlled by nuclear genes.
2. single recessive genes
- Sunflower dominant gene
3. The male sterile and male fertile line are observed in 1:1 ratio.
4. Used for production in Seed propagated and Vegetatively Propagated Crops.
CMS (Cytoplasmic Male Sterility)
1. It is controlled by cytoplasmic genes or plasmagens.
2. This can not used for Seed Propagated species because it is sterile.
3. If F4 is unstable, they turn fertile or sterile.
CGMS (Cytoplasmic-Genetic Male Sterility)
1. It is controlled by both Cytoplasmic and nuclear genes.
2. It consists of A and B line. A line sterile and B fertile AB:B 1:1
3. Used for production in Seed Propagated and Vegetatively Propagated Crops.
4. This is highly stable and no effect of temperature.
